# 🚀 Full-Stack App Setup Guide

Welcome to the **Full-Stack App**! This project has two main parts:

- **Client (React Frontend)** ➝ Located in the `client` folder.
- **Server (Node.js Backend)** ➝ Located in the `server` folder.

This guide will help you set up the project on your system.

---

## 🛠 Prerequisites (Before You Start)

### 1️⃣ **Install Node.js & npm**
Our backend requires **Node.js** and **npm** (Node Package Manager).  
If you don’t have them installed, follow these steps:

#### ➤ **Windows**
1. Download & install **Node.js** from [Node.js Official Website](https://nodejs.org/).
2. Verify installation by running:
   ```sh
   node -v
   npm -v
➤ Mac & Linux (Using NVM)
Install NVM (Node Version Manager):



curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.3/install.sh | bash
Restart the terminal, then install Node.js:



nvm install --lts
Verify installation:



node -v
npm -v
📂 Project Setup
🔹 1. Clone the Repository



git clone https://github.com/alphatechitco/AlphaConnectHub.git

🔹 2. Install Dependencies for Client & Server
Client (React)

cd client
npm install
npm start
This will install all necessary packages and start the React development server.

Server (Node.js)



cd server
npm install
node server.js
This will install backend dependencies and start the server.

⚙️ Environment Variables Setup
Your project requires some secret environment variables (.env).

📩 Contact the developer on Instagram to get the .env file
📍 Instagram Profile: @haxxaamm
📍 Instagram Link: 
https://www.instagram.com/haxxaamm?igsh=MTJsb3RwMnVzcWh1aA%3D%3D&utm_source=qr

How to Add .env File?
Create a .env file in the server folder.
Add the variables you received from the developer.
Example:
PORT=5000
DATABASE_URL=mongodb+srv://your_database_url
SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key


🎯 Running the Project
✅ Start Backend (Node.js)



cd server
node server.js
Runs the Node.js backend on localhost:5000.

✅ Start Frontend (React)

cd client
npm start
Runs the React app on localhost:3000.

🚀 Deployment
For production deployment:

Frontend: Deploy via Vercel, Netlify, or Firebase Hosting.
Backend: Deploy using Render, Railway, or a VPS (e.g., DigitalOcean, AWS, or Heroku).
